# Markdown Writing Rules (Markdownlint Compliant)

## Document Structure

### Required Elements

- **Single H1**: Each document must have exactly one H1 (`#`) as the first heading
- **Proper Heading Hierarchy**: Never skip heading levels  
  (H1 → H2 → H3, not H1 → H3)
- **Consistent Line Endings**: Use Unix-style line endings (LF, not CRLF)
- **End with Newline**: Files must end with a single newline character

### Line Length

- Maximum line length: 120 characters for content
- Exception: URLs, code blocks, and tables can exceed this limit
- Use line breaks for readability in long paragraphs

## Heading Rules

### Heading Format

- **ATX-style headings only**: Use `#` for headings, not underlines
- **Space after hash**: Always include space after `#` (✅ `# Title`, ❌ `#Title`)
- **No trailing punctuation**: Don't end headings with periods, colons, etc.
- **Blank lines around headings**: One blank line before and after each heading
- **No duplicate headings**: Each heading should be unique within the document

### Heading Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

# Document Title

## Section Heading

Content here.

### Subsection

More content.

❌ Incorrect:

#Document Title

## Section Heading.

Content here.
###Subsection
```

## List Rules

### Unordered Lists

- **Consistent markers**: Use `-` for all unordered lists (not `*` or `+`)
- **Proper indentation**: Use 2 spaces for nested lists
- **Blank lines**: Add blank lines around lists (except in nested lists)
- **Start at beginning**: Lists should start at the beginning of the line

### Ordered Lists

- **Sequential numbering**: Use `1.`, `2.`, `3.` (not all `1.`)
- **Period after number**: Always use period, not parenthesis `1)`
- **Consistent indentation**: Align text properly with first line

### List Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

- First item
- Second item
  - Nested item
  - Another nested
- Third item

1. First step
2. Second step
3. Third step

❌ Incorrect:

- First item

* Second item
  - Wrong indent

- Third item

1. First step

1) Second step
1) Third step
```

## Code Rules

### Inline Code

- **Backticks**: Use single backticks for inline code
- **No spaces**: No spaces inside backticks (✅ `code`, ❌ `code`)
- **Escape backticks**: Use double backticks if code contains backticks

### Code Blocks

- **Fenced blocks**: Use triple backticks (\`\`\`) not indented blocks
- **Language identifier**: Always specify language after opening backticks
- **Blank lines**: Surround code blocks with blank lines
- **No trailing spaces**: Remove trailing whitespace in code blocks

### Code Examples

````markdown
✅ Correct:

Use the `npm install` command.

```javascript
const example = "code";
console.log(example);
```
````

❌ Incorrect:

Use the `npm install` command.

```javascript
const example = "code"; // Indented block
console.log(example);
```

## Link Rules

### Link Format

- **No bare URLs**: Always use proper link syntax
- **Descriptive text**: Use meaningful link text, not "click here"
- **No spaces in URLs**: Use %20 or restructure if needed
- **Reference-style for repeated links**: Use references for links used
  multiple times

### Link Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

Check the [documentation](https://example.com/docs) for details.

Visit the [API Reference][api-ref] for more info.

[api-ref]: https://example.com/api

❌ Incorrect:

https://example.com/docs

[Click here](https://example.com/docs) for documentation.

[broken link](https://example.com/my docs)
```

## Emphasis Rules

### Bold and Italic

- **Consistent markers**: Use `**` for bold, `*` for italic
- **No spaces**: No spaces inside emphasis markers
- **Proper nesting**: Bold outside, italic inside when combining

#### Emphasis Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

This is **bold text** and this is _italic text_.

This is **_bold and italic_** text.

❌ Incorrect:

This is **bold text** and this is _italic text_.

This is ** bold text ** with spaces.
```

## Table Rules

### Table Format

- **Pipes and alignment**: Use pipes (`|`) with spaces for padding
- **Header separator**: Use at least 3 hyphens per column
- **Alignment markers**: Use `:` for alignment  
  (`:---` left, `:---:` center, `---:` right)
- **Consistent spacing**: Align columns for readability

### Table Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |
| -------- | :------: | -------: |
| Left     |  Center  |    Right |
| Data     |   Data   |     Data |

❌ Incorrect:

| Header 1  | Header 2 | Header 3 |
| --------- | -------- | -------- |
| Unaligned | Data     | Here     |
| More      | Stuff    | Things   |
```

## Blockquote Rules

- **Consistent markers**: Use `>` with space after
- **Lazy continuation**: Can omit `>` for paragraph continuation
- **Blank lines**: Separate blockquotes with blank lines

### Blockquote Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

> This is a blockquote.
> It can span multiple lines.

> Another quote here.

❌ Incorrect:

> No space after marker.
> This is wrong.
```

## Image Rules

- **Alt text required**: Always provide descriptive alt text
- **Consistent format**: Use same format as links
- **File references**: Use relative paths when possible

### Image Examples

```markdown
✅ Correct:

![Description of image](./images/example.png)

![Company Logo](https://example.com/logo.png)

❌ Incorrect:

![](./images/example.png) // Missing alt text

![ ](./images/example.png) // Empty alt text
```

## HTML Rules

- **Avoid when possible**: Use Markdown syntax over HTML
- **Allowed elements**: Only use HTML when Markdown can't achieve the result
- **Self-closing tags**: Include the slash for self-closing tags
- **No deprecated elements**: Don't use `<center>`, `<font>`, etc.

## Whitespace Rules

### Spaces

- **No trailing spaces**: Remove all trailing whitespace
- **No multiple spaces**: Use single spaces except in code blocks
- **No hard tabs**: Use spaces for indentation (2 spaces standard)

### Blank Lines

- **Single blank lines**: Never use multiple consecutive blank lines
- **Around blocks**: Use blank lines around headings, lists, code blocks
- **Document boundaries**: No blank lines at start, single newline at end

## File Naming

- **Lowercase with hyphens**: Use `my-document.md` not `My_Document.md`
- **Descriptive names**: Use clear, descriptive file names
- **Consistent extensions**: Use `.md` for Markdown, `.mdx` for MDX

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### Don't

- Mix heading styles (ATX and Setext)
- Use HTML when Markdown suffices
- Create inconsistent list markers
- Skip heading levels
- Use trailing spaces or multiple blank lines
- Forget alt text for images
- Use bare URLs without link syntax
- End headings with punctuation
- Mix emphasis styles (\*\* vs \_\_)

### Do

- Maintain consistent formatting throughout
- Use proper Markdown syntax
- Include descriptive link and image text
- Follow proper heading hierarchy
- Keep line lengths reasonable
- Use reference-style links for repeated URLs
- Add blank lines for readability
- Validate with markdownlint

